bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:plmn-type.description: Type of Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN).

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:plmnid.description: PLMN ID consists of Mobile Country Code (MCC) and Mobile Network Code (MNC) {{bibref|3GPP-TS.23.003}}, {{bibref|3GPP-TS.24.008}}. Mobile Country Code consists of three digits and uniquely identifies the country of domicile of the subscriber. Mobile Network Code consists of two or three digits and identifies the Home PLMN within a country. For a 2-digit MNC the total string length of {{param}} is 5.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:lac.description: Location Area Code (LAC) as defined in SIB 1 {{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.331}}. The concatenation of PLMN ID (MCC+MNC) and LAC uniquely identifies the LAI (Location Area ID) {{bibref|3GPP-TS.23.003}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:rac.description: Routing Area Code (RAC) as defined in SIB 1 {{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.331}}. The concatenation of PLMN ID (MCC+MNC), LAC, and RAC uniquely identifies the RAI (Routing Area ID) {{bibref|3GPP-TS.23.003}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:cell-id.description: Cell Identity as defined in SIB3 {{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.331|Section10.3.2.2}}. {{bibref|3GPP-TS.24.008}}

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:pcpich-tx-power.description: Primary Common Pilot Channel (CPICH) power level on SIB 5/6 {{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.331|Section10.3.6.55}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:csg-indicator.description: The CSG-indicator Information Element (IE) in the Master Information Block reflects the access mode of the CSG cell. It is hence dependent on the value of {{param|.AccessMgmt.UMTS.AccessMode}}. If {{true}} the CSG-indicator IE is present, reflecting closed access to the CSG cell. If {{false}} the CSG-indicator IE is absent, reflecting the access mode as "not a closed-access". {{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.331|Section 10.2.48.8.1}}

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:csgid.description: Defines the Closed Subscriber Group of the Access Control List. FAP broadcasts this CSG ID in SIB3 {{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.331|Section10.3.2.8}} depending on the AccessMode.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:uarfcndl-list.description: {{list}} Each item is a UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number (UARFCN} in the DL direction dedicated to the CSG cells. {{param}} is broadcast in SIB 11bis {{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.331|Section 10.2.48.8.14a}}. The corresponding UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number (UARFCN} in the UL direction is derived based on the fixed offset applicable for the frequency band.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:rem-umts-wcdma-cel.description: Key value for this object, which could be an item of a list.

rem-umts-wcdma-cell-key.description: Key value for this object, which could be an item of a list.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:scan-status.description: Indicates the current status of this scan.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:error-details.description: Provides more detail when the {{param|ScanStatus}} is either {{enum|Error|ScanStatus}} or {{enum|Error_TIMEOUT|ScanStatus}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:last-scan-time.description: The time of the last UMTS system radio environment measurement.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:max-cell-entries.description: The maximum number of entries available in the {{object|.REM.UMTS.WCDMA.Cell.{i}.}} table.

in-service-handling.description: FAP REM behavior with respect to ongoing active connections.

scan-on-boot.description: Enables or disables Radio Environment Measurement during the FAP start up.

scan-periodically.description: Enable Periodic Radio Environment Measurement on all enabled RAT.

periodic-interval.description: When {{param|ScanPeriodically}} is {{true}}, this value indicates the interval in {{units}} which REM is performed while the FAP service is enabled.

periodic-time.description: An absolute time reference in UTC to determine when the CPE will initiate the periodic REM. Each REM MUST occur at (or as soon as possible after) this reference time plus or minus an integer multiple of the {{param|PeriodicInterval}}. {{param}} is used only to set the "phase" of the REM. The actual value of {{param}} can be arbitrarily far into the past or future. For example, if {{param|PeriodicInterval}} is 86400 (a day) and if {{param}} is set to UTC midnight on some day (in the past, present, or future) then periodic REMs will occur every day at UTC midnight. These MUST begin on the very next midnight, even if {{param}} refers to a day in the future. The Unknown Time value defined in {{bibref|TR-106a2|Section 3.2}} indicates that no particular time reference is specified. That is, the CPE MAY locally choose the time reference, and needs only to adhere to the specified PeriodicInformInterval. If absolute time is not available to the CPE, its periodic REM behavior MUST be the same as if {{param}} parameter was set to the Unknown Time value.

scan-timeout.description: Specifies the time-out value in {{units}}, measured from the start of the REM scan, before the REM scan will time out.

scan-status.description: Indicates the current status of this scan.

error-details.description: Provides more detail when the {{param|ScanStatus}} is either {{enum|Error|ScanStatus}} or {{enum|Error_TIMEOUT|ScanStatus}}.

last-scan-time.description: The time of the last UMTS system radio environment measurement.

max-cell-entries.description: The maximum number of entries available in the {{object|.REM.UMTS.WCDMA.Cell.{i}.}} table.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:band-indicator.description: Indicates how to interpret the BCCH ARFCN.

Mobile Country Code consists of three digits and uniquely identifies the country of domicile of the subscriber. Mobile Network Code consists of two or three digits and identifies the Home PLMN within a country. For a 2-digit MNC the total string length of the PLMNID is 5.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:lac.description: Location Area Code (LAC) as defined in SIB1 {{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.331}}. The concatenation of PLMN ID (MCC+MNC) and LAC uniquely identifies the LAI (Location Area ID) {{bibref|3GPP-TS.23.003}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:rac.description: Routing Area Code (RAC) consists of up to 3 numerical characters. The concatenation of PLMN ID (MCC+MNC), LAC, and RAC uniquely identifies the Routing Area ID (RAI). {{bibref|3GPP-TS.23.003|Section 4.2}} {{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.413|Section 9.2.3.7}}

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:rssi.description: Received signal level in {{units}} of the BCCH carrier.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:eutra-carrier-arfc.description: Indicates the ARFCN of this carrier frequency. Corresponds to parameter dl-CarrierFreq in SIB5 in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.3.1}}, and parameter NDL in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.101|Section 5.7.3}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:phy-cell-id.description: Physical cell ID of the detected EUTRAN cell, as specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.101|Section 5.6}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:rsrp.description: Received RSRP level of the detected EUTRA cell, specified in {{units}}, as specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.214|Section 5.1.1}}. The reporting range is specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.133|Section 9.1.4}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:rsrq.description: Received RSRQ level of the detected EUTRA cell, specified in {{units}}, as specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.214|Section 5.1.3}}. Actual measured values range between -24.0 {{units}} and 0.0 {{units}} in steps of 0.5 {{units}}. The value of {{param}} divided by 10 yields the actual measured value. Only values in multiple of 5 are valid.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:rssi.description: E-UTRA Carrier Received Signal Strength Indicator (RSSI), specified in {{units}}, as specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.214|Section 5.1.3}}. It comprises the linear average of the total received power (in [W]) observed only in OFDM symbols containing reference symbols for antenna port 0, in the measurement bandwidth, over N number of resource blocks by the UE from all sources, including co-channel serving and non-serving cells, adjacent channel interference, thermal noise etc.

eutra-carrier-arfcn.description: Indicates the ARFCN of this carrier frequency. Corresponds to parameter dl-CarrierFreq in SIB5 in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.3.1}}, and parameter NDL in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.101|Section 5.7.3}}.

phy-cell-id.description: Physical cell ID of the detected EUTRAN cell, as specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.101|Section 5.6}}.

rsrp.description: Received RSRP level of the detected EUTRA cell, specified in {{units}}, as specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.214|Section 5.1.1}}. The reporting range is specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.133|Section 9.1.4}}.

rsrq.description: Received RSRQ level of the detected EUTRA cell, specified in {{units}}, as specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.214|Section 5.1.3}}. Actual measured values range between -24.0 {{units}} and 0.0 {{units}} in steps of 0.5 {{units}}. The value of {{param}} divided by 10 yields the actual measured value. Only values in multiple of 5 are valid.

rssi.description: E-UTRA Carrier Received Signal Strength Indicator (RSSI), specified in {{units}}, as specified in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.214|Section 5.1.3}}. It comprises the linear average of the total received power (in [W]) observed only in OFDM symbols containing reference symbols for antenna port 0, in the measurement bandwidth, over N number of resource blocks by the UE from all sources, including co-channel serving and non-serving cells, adjacent channel interference, thermal noise etc.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:plmnid.description: PLMN ID consists of Mobile Country Code (MCC) and Mobile Network Code (MNC) {{bibref|3GPP-TS.23.003}}, {{bibref|3GPP-TS.24.008}}. Mobile Country Code consists of three digits and uniquely identifies the country of domicile of the subscriber. Mobile Network Code consists of two or three digits and identifies the Home PLMN within a country. For a 2-digit MNC the total string length of {{param}} is 5.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:cell-reserved-for-.description: Indicates whether the cell is reserved for operator use or not. If {{true}}, it is reserved. If {{false}}, it is not reserved. Corresponds to "reserved" "notReserved" respectively as defined in PLMN-IdentityInfo in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.2.2}}.

plmnid.description: PLMN ID consists of Mobile Country Code (MCC) and Mobile Network Code (MNC) {{bibref|3GPP-TS.23.003}}, {{bibref|3GPP-TS.24.008}}. Mobile Country Code consists of three digits and uniquely identifies the country of domicile of the subscriber. Mobile Network Code consists of two or three digits and identifies the Home PLMN within a country. For a 2-digit MNC the total string length of {{param}} is 5.

cell-reserved-for-operator-use.description: Indicates whether the cell is reserved for operator use or not. If {{true}}, it is reserved. If {{false}}, it is not reserved. Corresponds to "reserved" "notReserved" respectively as defined in PLMN-IdentityInfo in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.2.2}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:dl-bandwidth.description: Downlink transmission bandwidth, specified in number of {{units}}. Corresponds to parameter dl_Bandwidth in Master Information Block in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.2.2}}. and to parameter NRB in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.101|Table 5.6-1}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:ul-bandwidth.description: Uplink transmission bandwidth, specified in number of {{units}}. Corresponds to parameter ul_Bandwidth in SIB2 in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.3.1}}. and to parameter NRB in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.101|Table 5.6-1}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:rs-tx-power.description: The downlink reference-signal transmit power, specified in {{units}}. Defined as the linear average over the power contributions (in W) of all resource elements that carry cell-specific reference signals within the operating system bandwidth. Corresponds to parameter referenceSignalPower in SIB4 as a part of PDSCH-Config IE in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.3.2}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:tac.description: Tracking Area Code that is common for all the PLMNs listed. Corresponds to trackingAreaCode as specified in SIB1 in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.2.2}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:cell-id.description: Defines the cell identify, defines as a 28-bit binary number. Corresponds to cellIdentity as specified in SIB1 in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.2.2 and Section 6.3.4}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:cell-barred.description: Indicates whether the cell is barred or not. If {{true}}, the cell is barred. If {{false}}, the cell is not barred. Corresponds to cellBarred as specified in SIB1 in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.2.2}} and {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.304}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:csg-indication.description: Indicates whether CSG is used in this cell or not. If {{true}}, the UE is only allowed to access the cell if the CSG identity matches an entry in the allowed CSG list that the UE has stored. Corresponds to csg-Indication as specified in SIB1 in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.2.2}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:csg-identity.description: Defines the CSG ID value if {{param|CSGIndication}} parameter indicates that CSG is used in this cell. Corresponds to csg-Identity as specified in SIB1 in {{bibref|3GPP-TS.36.331|Section 6.2.2}}.

periodic-interval.description: When {{param|ScanPeriodically}} is {{true}}, this value indicates the interval in {{units}} which REM is performed while the FAP service is enabled.

periodic-time.description: An absolute time reference in UTC to determine when the CPE will initiate the periodic REM. Each REM MUST occur at (or as soon as possible after) this reference time plus or minus an integer multiple of the {{param|PeriodicInterval}}. {{param}} is used only to set the "phase" of the REM. The actual value of {{param}} can be arbitrarily far into the past or future. For example, if {{param|PeriodicInterval}} is 86400 (a day) and if {{param}} is set to UTC midnight on some day (in the past, present, or future) then periodic REMs will occur every day at UTC midnight. These MUST begin on the very next midnight, even if {{param}} refers to a day in the future. The Unknown Time value defined in {{bibref|TR-106a2|Section 3.2}} indicates that no particular time reference is specified. That is, the CPE MAY locally choose the time reference, and needs only to adhere to the specified PeriodicInformInterval. If absolute time is not available to the CPE, its periodic REM behavior MUST be the same as if {{param}} parameter was set to the Unknown Time value.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:p-access-net-info-.description: This string will be populated as the value for P-Access-Network-Info header. This header is generated by the device. See {{bibref|3GPP2-X.S0059}} and {{bibref|RFC3455}}.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:sip-auth-capabilit.description: Represents the SIP authentication mechanisms supported by this device.

fcsuri.description: The request URI for MESSAGE method sent to Femtocell Convergence Server (FCS). The string MUST contain a URI as defined in {{bibref|RFC3986}}. The device MUST support SIP URI and MAY support other URI schemes.

out-going-proxy-uri.description: The request URI for Outgoing Proxy. The string MUST contain a URI as defined in {{bibref|RFC3986}}. The device MUST support SIP URI and MAY support other URI schemes.

p-access-net-info-header.description: This string will be populated as the value for P-Access-Network-Info header. This header is generated by the device. See {{bibref|3GPP2-X.S0059}} and {{bibref|RFC3455}}.

realm.description: The FQDN or IP Address representing the Home Domain of the device. The request URI for REGISTER will be formed by prefixing "sip:" to this value.

impi.description: The "IP Multimedia Private Identity" (IMPI). This value is ignored when {{param|SIPAuthMethod}} is set to {{enum|TNA|SIPAuthMethod}}.

sip-password.description: Password to Authenticate the IMS core. This value is ignored when {{param|SIPAuthMethod}} is set to {{enum|TNA|SIPAuthMethod}}.

sip-auth-method.description: Represents the authentication method used by this device for SIP registration. If value is {{enum|SIPDigest}}, the {{param|SIPPassword}} MUST not be {{empty}}. If value is {{enum|TNA}}, {{param|SIPPassword}} and {{param|IMPI}} are ignored.

sip-local-port.description: Local port number for initiating SIP traffic.

rtp-port-low-limit.description: The low limit of port number for originating and receiving RTP/RTCP traffic.

rtp-port-high-limit.description: The high limit of port number for originating and receiving RTP/RTCP traffic.

sip-reg-expiry.description: SIP registration expiry value, as defined in {{bibref|RFC3261}}.

sip-session-expiry.description: SIP session timer expiry value, in {{units}}, as defined in {{bibref|RFC4028}}.

timer-t1.description: Value of SIP timer T1, in {{units}}, as defined in {{bibref|RFC3261}}.

timer-t2.description: Value of SIP timer T2, in {{units}}, as defined in {{bibref|RFC3261}}.

timer-t4.description: Value of SIP timer T4, in {{units}}, as defined in {{bibref|RFC3261}}.

t3210.description: This value specifies how much time to wait, in {{units}}, before time out on location update accept/reject. See {{bibref|3GPP2-A.S0014}}.

enable.description: Enables or disables the whole SIP object and allows the setup or release of SIP associations and their related streams.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:status.description: The status of this SCTP association entry.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:primary-peer-addre.description: The primary IP address of the peer SCTP association entity.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:local-port.description: The local SCTP port number used for this SCTP association.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:in-streams.description: The number of Inbound Streams according to the negotiation at association start-up.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:out-streams.description: The number of Outbound Streams according to the negotiation at association start-up.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:start-time.description: The start Time for the present SCTP association.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:discontinuity.description: The time of the last discontinuity.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:out-of-blues.description: The number of correctly formed SCTP packets, including the proper checksum, but for which the receiver was unable to identify an appropriate association.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:checksum-errors.description: The number of SCTP packets received with an invalid checksum.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:out-ctrl-chunks.description: The number of SCTP control chunks sent (retransmissions are not included).

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:out-order-chunks.description: The number of SCTP ordered data chunks sent (retransmissions are not included).

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:out-unorder-chunks.description: The number of SCTP unordered chunks (data chunks in which the U bit is set to 1) sent (retransmissions are not included).

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:in-ctrl-chunks.description: The number of SCTP control chunks received (no duplicate chunks included).

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:in-order-chunks.description: The number of SCTP ordered data chunks received (no duplicate chunks included).

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:in-unorder-chunks.description: The number of SCTP unordered chunks (data chunks in which the U bit is set to 1) received (no duplicate chunks included).

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:frag-usr-msgs.description: The number of user messages that have been sent fragmented.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:reasm-usr-msgs.description: The number of user messages that have been received fragmented and submitted to the reassembly process.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:out-sctp-packs.description: The number of SCTP packets sent. Retransmitted DATA chunks are included.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:in-sctp-packs.description: The number of SCTP packets received. Duplicates are included.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:discontinuity.description: The time of the last discontinuity.

enable.description: Enables or disables the whole SCTP object and allows the setup or release of SCTP associations and their related streams.

max-association-retransmits.description: Maximum number of consecutive retransmissions to a peer before an endpoint considers that the peer is unreachable and closes the association.

rto-initial.description: Initial value for Retransmit timeout in {{units}}. A retransmission time value of zero means immediate retransmission.

rto-max.description: Maximum value for Retransmit timeout in {{units}}. A retransmission time value of zero means immediate retransmission.

rto-min.description: Minimum value for Retransmit timeout in {{units}}. A retransmission time value of zero means immediate retransmission. The value of this parameter MUST be lower than or equal to {{param|RTOMax}}.

val-cookie-life.description: Valid cookie life in the 4-way start-up handshake procedure in {{units}}.

reasm-usr-msgs.description: The number of user messages that have been received fragmented and submitted to the reassembly process.

in-sctp-packs.description: The number of SCTP packets received. Duplicates are included.

discontinuity.description: The time of the last discontinuity.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:lost-far-end-packe.description: The number of Far End Lost RTP packets.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:underruns.description: Total number of times the receive jitter buffer has underrun for a CS-domain RAB.

bbf-tr-196-2-0-3-full:max-rtt.description: The maximum Round Trip Time in {{units}} as computed by the source. {{bibref|RFC3550}}
